<p>14.&nbsp;<strong>Order Terms and Conditions</strong>.</p>

<p>Order and Payment</p>

<p>If you wish to make an order of your 3D model scan (the &ldquo;3D Scan&rdquo;) you may order 3D printing and shipping services and purchase them through Artec Services.</p>

<p>All print jobs in respect of duly confirmed and paid orders is performed by contractors engaged by Artec (each, a &ldquo;Printing Provider&rdquo;).</p>

<p>All prices and amounts shown on Artec Services are in U.S. Dollars (USD), unless otherwise noted. If you submits request through Artec Services to purchase 3D printing and shipping services, you agree that all charges, taxes and shipping/handling fees will automatically be charged to your credit or card. Credit and debit cards accepted for payment are: Visa, Mastercard, Discover and Amex. Other ways of payment may be available on the Site from time to time. Artec requires each order to be fully paid, including shipping and handling fees, if applicable, before Artec completes an order. Artec will not start working on a print job until Artec receives the full payment, including applicable taxes and shipping/handling fees.</p>

<p>Once a print job has been submitted by you and is already &quot;In Production&quot;, no changes are allowed to the 3D Scan, job characteristics, or printing turnaround time.</p>

<p>Return Policy</p>

<p>Artec strives to provide our clients with the best possible experience. If you are not satisfied with your order for any reason, please contact our customer service department. Our representative will document your complaint and create a ticket for your reference.</p>

<p>Artec will issue a 100% refund (less shipping charges) for any defective print order if such claim has been provided within the time limits provided in these Terms of Use.</p>

<p>Please note that to receive a refund the defect affecting quality of 3D Scan must be the fault of Artec. Artec will not issue refunds for poor print orders that resulted from defective 3D Scans. Artec will not issue a refund in case of inaccurate uploading of the 3D Scan to the Site. Artec will not issue a refund and will not be liable in case 3D Scan is not exactly the same as shown when uploaded by you through Artec Services. Differences may result from the color quality of images, the difficulty of showing on screen the texture of a material or, without limitation, technical adaptation. These differences should not be interpreted as lack of conformity and shall not justify a &ldquo;defect&rdquo; and shall not cause a refund. Determination of defect is at the discretion of Artec.</p>

<p>Refund will not be made and Artec will not be responsible for consequences inherent to the individual user, such as allergic reactions to materials used for manufacturing (printing) of 3D Scan, or if the personalized 3D Scan fails to satisfy you due to your personal taste.</p>

<p>Refund will not be made and Artec will not be responsible for consequences of whatever nature if Artec and/or Printing Provider and/or Shipping Provider refuses to provide a service on the grounds specified in Section 6 of these Terms.</p>

<p>In most cases, you will be requested to submit digital photos documenting the product defect and/or ship the defective products back to Artec&rsquo;s customer service at your own cost. Accepting these Terms you agree to such return policy. All policies are subject to change without prior notification.</p>

<p>Printing Accuracy</p>

<p>3D scanning and 3D printing are relatively new processes with many limitations. Because of inherent limitations with the scanning and printing process, the accuracy of the reproduction and printing of the object scanned and printed through Artec is not guaranteed. By placing an order with Artec through Artec Services you agree to this limitation.</p>

<p>Printing Turnaround Time</p>

<p>Printing turnaround time depends on the Printing Provider and begins once your 3D Scan is uploaded to the Site, attached to your printing job, the order has been confirmed for printing, and full payment has been made. Please note that there is no production or shipping on Saturdays, Sundays and Holidays. As a result, these days are not considered when calculating printing turnaround time. In addition, while production turnaround does not include mailing, or shipping transit times, and you should allow additional business days for delivery.</p>

<p>Shipping</p>

<p>You will need to complete the shipping details on the Site. All shipping is currently done via international carriers engaged by the Printing Provider (the &ldquo;Shipping Provider&rdquo;).</p>

<p>Usually, estimated shipping transit time is based on the number of business days in transit and does not include weekends, holidays or the day the package is picked up by the carrier. For instance, a product shipped 2nd Day Air and picked up on a Thursday would be delivered by end of day Monday. Shipping transit times vary, and Artec assumes no responsibility for delays caused by Shipping Provider, shipping carriers, weather or any damages resulting from the failure to receive a job on time. Your order may arrive late due to unforeseen delays in delivery service, the breakdown of equipment, illness, etc. Artec will not be liable for any failure in shipment and you will refer and submit all your claims, if any, to the Shipping Provider.</p>

